"{\"uid\": \"wtvq.com-special-olympics-summer-games-return-to-eku\", \"text\": \"Sections  About  Connect With Us  1/0    MADISON COUNTY, Ky. (ABC36 NEWS NOW) -In Madison County, the Special Olympics State Summer Games are returning to Eastern Kentucky University (EKU) in Richmond this week. Organizers expect more than a thousand Special Olympics athletes and over 500 volunteers from across the state to participate.  The games will take place from Friday through Sunday, with a number of events leading up to them. Staff and volunteers will begin arriving on campus Wednesday.  Additionally, the final leg of the Law Enforcement Torch Run will kick off at the State Capitol on Friday morning, marking the official start of the games.  RelatedFree Thanksgiving Day meal at the Catholic Action CenterGobble Grease Toss returns Friday for post-Thanksgiving oil recyclingLexington Police remembering Lt. John ThomasMan O War Harley-Davidson Customer Appreciation Night and Holiday Specials  CountdownTo Christmasdays leftWhat's On TV NowComplete TV ProgrammingLocal Events  Local Events              \\u00a9 2025 WTVQ.    Talk to ABC 36 News anchors, reporters and meteorologists. When you see news happening, share it! We'd love to hear from you.  859-299-3636|news36@wtvq.com  6940 Man O' War Blvd. Lexington, KY 40509  We live, work and play right here in Central Kentucky. We are your neighbors. We celebrate community and we tell your stories. We are the most trusted source for local news.  Download the ABC 36 News App on your smart phone or tablet device to receive breaking news and weather push notifications the minute it happens.  Mobile App|WEATHER App|WTVQ Email Sign Up\"}"